The 2019 NBBF Men’s Premier League will tip off October 13 and ends November 30, 2019 in both the Atlantic and Savannah Conferences. The first phase of the Atlantic Conference will hold in Akure, while the Savannah Conference is billed for Zaria between October 12 and 22. The second phase of the league will take place from November 2 to 12. M.K.O Abiola Stadium will host the second phase of the Savannah Conference, while the Atlantic Conference will hold at the Ilorin Township stadium. Top 4 teams in each conference will qualify for the National Final 8 from November 24 to 30. Atlantic teams are Oluyole Warriors, Customs of Lagos, Kwara Falcons, Hoops and Read of Lagos, Delta Force, Police Baton and Raptors. Others are Dodan Warriors, Lagos Islanders, Invaders of Ekiti, Coal City and Akure Raiders. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The Savannah Conference teams are Kano Pillars, Bauchi Nets, Gombe Bulls, Kada Stars, Defender of Abuja, Niger Potters, Mark Mentors (Abuja), Plateau Peaks, Nigeria Army (Zaria) and Benue Braves (Makurdi). According to NBBF President, Musa Kida, exciting times await teams, players, fans of the league with the federation in discussion with prospective sponsors. “We are currently at an advanced stage of discussion with interested parties who are thinking of investing in the men’s league with our ultimate goal of getting the various leagues back on TV.” The League champion will represent Nigeria in the inaugural Basketball Africa League to be organized by NBA in conjunction with FIBA Africa.